server sitting there,

00:47:29.470 --> 00:47:32.710
all the Macs boot up
off a tiny little image,

00:47:32.710 --> 00:47:35.950
and then I could have a 10
gigabyte image being pushed out,

00:47:36.200 --> 00:47:40.500
not over multicast, or not over unicast,
but multicast.

00:47:40.560 --> 00:47:46.000
I can decide which method I want to use,
so I can be incredibly efficient.

00:47:46.330 --> 00:47:48.940
and if I use Multicast,
that means all the machines

00:47:49.000 --> 00:47:51.440
don't have to be started at once,
they just start getting the bits.

00:47:51.440 --> 00:47:55.380
