00:49:06.900 --> 00:49:10.290
the package that I created.

00:49:10.840 --> 00:49:13.520
And if necessary,
reboot the system automatically.

00:49:13.870 --> 00:49:15.700
There's no fees for this.

00:49:15.960 --> 00:49:17.930
You bought the server.

00:49:18.360 --> 00:49:22.440
So net install is a great
way to deploy packages.

00:49:22.450 --> 00:49:25.080
And if you're a shell scripter
and you have scripts that you need

00:49:25.080 --> 00:49:27.530
to do cleanup or something else,
you can have what are called

00:49:27.690 --> 00:49:28.760
payload-free packages.

00:49:28.780 --> 00:49:32.510
These are packages that don't
really have an item to deploy,

00:49:32.510 --> 00:49:35.380
but they run scripts for you.

00:49:35.550 --> 00:49:37.130
That's not too hard for
me to go tell users,

00:49:37.230 --> 00:49:39.000
hold down the N key.

00:49:39.040 --> 00:49:41.330
You got five minutes,
go get a cup of coffee.

00:49:41.350 --> 00:49:43.640
And we can use SSH to also do this.

